stories.title: Kallis steers South Africa home
stories.subTitle: India v South Africa, 1st ODI, Hyderabad
stories.summary: South Africa's faster men began with a bang, rattling the Indian top order with seam, pace and bounce, before their batsmen strung together vital partnerships, held their nerve and wrapped up an absorbing opening game of the five-match series at Hyderabad

stories.title: 'We know that they're beatable' - Dravid
stories.subTitle: India v South Africa, 2nd ODI, Bangalore
stories.summary: Rahul Dravid denies that South Africa's fast bowlers got the better of his side in the firsft match at Hyderabad, maintaining that it was simply an off day for India. Greg Chappell didn't let on to much, but says that India learnt a fair

stories.title: The die has been cast for South Africa
stories.subTitle: India v South Africa, 2nd ODI, Bangalore
stories.summary: South Africa pricked India's win-bubble three days ago, and stand on that threshold of a remarkable record that appeared unthinkable when they struggled to a 0-1 Test reverse in India a year ago.
stories.byline: The Preview by Dileep Premachandran at Bangalore

stories.title: Dravid predicts close series
stories.subTitle: South Africa tour of India, 2005-06
stories.summary: Predicting a close series against South Africa, Rahul Dravid, the Indian captain, says that his team will strive to bounce back with an improved performance in the second one-dayer to be played in Bangalore on November 19

stories.title: Harbhajan fined for conduct
stories.subTitle: India v South Africa, 1st ODI, Hyderabad
stories.summary: Harbhajan Singh, has been fined 25% of his match fee for breaching the ICC Code of Conduct during the first ODI against South Africa

stories.title: 'Batting under pressure, I concentrate more' - Yuvraj
